						<summary>

						<p>Thee fragments of slab lying in the Aṅkāḷamma temple.</p>						

						<p>Kākatīya: Pratāpa Rudra.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1240, Kāḷayukta, Āśvayuja śu. 11, Thursday,</hi> corresponding to 1318 A.D., October 6. However, the week day is Friday.</p>						

						<p>Fragmentary. It registers gifts of land at several places made by <hi rend="italic">Mahāsāmanta</hi> Cheṟaku Mahēśvara Reḍḍi who was ruling over Kaṁnāḍu for worship of god Mūlasthāna Siddhanāthadēva of Vēlpunūru.</p>						

						</summary>
